The paper discusses the safety aspects of human-robot co-worker teams in a manufacturing environment, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of addressing human-centric research questions, indicating a potential fit for the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of learning machines and algorithms suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The need for safety assurance in the context of flexible manufacturing environments suggests a potential fit for the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the integration of safety considerations into algorithms, indicating a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
